        'Skill is, at its most fundamental level, the ability to make finer and finer distinctions.',
        'This idea comes out of ecological psychology and the work of James Gibson, but the practical reality of it shows up in every domain if you know to look for it. The wine expert who can taste the difference between two vintages from the same producer, the same year. The jazz musician who hears the quarter-tone flatness in someone else\'s pitch that most listeners would never catch. The surgeon who can feel, through the instrument in her hand, the difference between two types of tissue. The investor who reads a balance sheet and notices what\'s wrong in thirty seconds when an MBA student would stare at it for an hour and see nothing.',
