        'When you look at skill development through a perceptual lens, the whole story of becoming expert reads differently.',
        'Early in any skill journey, the main experience is overwhelm. Too much is happening, too fast, and you don\'t know what matters. Beginners often describe feeling like they can\'t track everything — they miss the obvious cues, they respond to the wrong signals, they get caught by surprises that experts would have anticipated. This is accurate. They genuinely are not perceiving most of what\'s happening. The perceptual vocabulary is too sparse.',
