        'There is no shortcut through this journey. The differentiations take the time they take. The transitions can\'t be forced. But they can be vastly accelerated by the right practice conditions, and vastly delayed — potentially indefinitely — by the wrong ones. Most people with years of experience and stuck plateaus are not doing the wrong volume of practice. They\'re doing the wrong kind.',
